In this case only 3% of parents noted that by them it is boring.
Professor Larson notes that he does not have data about which would be similar data about the boredom now, 21 year later.
However, he knows that “to the teenage period is fallen the peak of tendency toward the boredom”, in essence because to children and for adolescents they do not make possible entirely to decide how it to study.
Let us return to my initial question: boredom is useful?
Sometimes no, because in the extreme manifestations it, as show studies, can push slightly people to the absurd and dangerous physical actions, risky games of chance or abuse of the specific substances in the attempts to get rid of the boredom.
From the other side, many philosophers and writers thought about the connection between the boredom and creation, speaks professor Vodanovich, who dedicated to the study of this problem of more than two decades.
“So our brain prompts to us that it follows to study something other; this is boredom”, tell in Gary Marcus, professor of psychology at the New York university.
However, this brain itself does not always know how precisely it is better to study.
If to you it will be boring and you will direct this energy toward the game on the guitar or culinary experiences, you will make to yourselves better.
However, if you will begin to watch TV, they will become better only to some period, and soon this it will pass.
Therefore, if your child is bored and you give to it iPad, it will cease to be bored; however, it will not learn to fight with the boredom independently or by somehow other method to govern its time and employment, says professor Fenske.
“A such habits of independent regulation are engaged in the most different situations”, it asserts.
Your child learns not only to independently occupy himself something, he also learns self-control generally.
I do not think that the boredom must be somehow extolled.
However, to consider it its something poor also does not stand.
Rather one should learn to feel itself comfortably even out of the continuous flow of actions and technologies.
Professor Eastwood is agreeable with this.
“We see this so that we should more frequently experience boredom, with the fact that boredom - this extremely unpleasant, unquenchable desire to study something that comprehended”, he, says.
In reality people attempt somehow to be turned off from constant concerns and it is simple to be weakened.
